<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                    <head>No. 151.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Denby</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-18"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 18, 1887</date>.
                            (Received April 12.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 311.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the first
                        installment of the amount agreed to be paid on account of the losses of the
                        Methodist Episcopal mission at Chungking, 5,000 taels, was paid by the local
                        authorities at the time agreed on.</p>
                    <p>It has been received by Mr. Frank S. Gamewell, superintendent of the
                        mission.</p>
                    <p>1 have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Denby</hi>.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>